Ascii.desc: The password and salt use only ASCII characters. Some implementations of PBES2 assume that either password and/or salt contain only printable characters. This flag allows to select an appropriate subset of tests for such implementations.

Basic.desc: Basic test vectors use the simplest possible inputs. These inputs often overlap with inputs from standards and RFCs. One goal of such test vectors is to simply detect distinct algorithms.

InvalidParameter.desc: The test vector uses an invalid parameter.

NonUtf8.desc: Either password or the salt are not valid UTF-8 strings. Some implementations require that inputs are valid UTF-8 encodings. The purpose of this flag is to make it easier to skip test cases that cannot be tested with such implementations.

Printable.desc: The password and salt use only printable characters. Some implementations of PBES2 assume that either password and/or salt contain only printable characters. This flag allows to select an appropriate subset of tests for such implementations.

Pseudorandom.desc: The test vector has been generated pseudorandomly.

Utf8.desc: The password and salt are valid UTF-8 strings. Some implementations use inputs of type string and encode these strings using UTF-8 before passing them to PBES2. This test vector contains an inputs that are valid UTF-8 encodings.
